the broken tower is a 2011 american black-and-white student film directed , written , produced , edited by and starring james franco . the film was made by franco as his masters thesis for his mfa in filmmaking from new york university . the film is about american poet hart crane . franco appears in the starring role as crane along with michael shannon as one of crane 's lovers . the broken tower made its world premiere in april 2011 at boston college . it was shown at the 2011 los angeles film festival ( &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ) in june and released on dvd in 2012 . the film includes the recitation by franco of several of crane 's poems both as voice-over additions to the film , as well as actual readings of several poems rendered by franco as portraying crane himself .